data.title: ROUNDUP: N.B.A. PLAYOFFS; Prince's 24 Help Pistons Oust Bucks
data.meta_description: Detroit Pistons defeat Milwaukee Bucks, 91-77, to win first-round playoff series, 4-1; photo (S)
data.text:
Tayshaun Prince had 24 points and a career-high 8 assists and 9 rebounds as the Detroit Pistons used a strong third quarter to take control in a 91-77 victory over the Milwaukee Bucks last night to win their first-round Eastern Conference playoff series, 4-1.

Playing at home in Auburn Hills, Mich., the Pistons took control with a 30-point third quarter after scoring just 39 points in the first half and leading by 7.

Chauncey Billups added 19 points and 6 assists, and Richard Hamilton scored 18.

''We just ran into a better team,'' said Michael Redd, who led the Bucks with 22 points.

The Pistons move on to face the Nets, the two-time defending Eastern Conference champions, on Monday in the conference semifinals.
